  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Adipocytokines play an important role in joint inflammation in patients with knee
      osteoarthritis as measured by ultrasound and high sensitivity protein-C reactive.
      Adipocytokines could be the link between osteoarthritis and cardiovascular risk factors more
      prevalent in these patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
